 integer nn; //Counter for number of iterations
 
 reg [0:r-1]parity;
 reg [size-1:0] min1 [0:r-1];
 reg [size-1:0] min2 [0:r-1];
 
 wire[0:r-1]temp_parity;
 wire[size-1:0] temp_min1 [0:r-1];
 wire[size-1:0] temp_min2 [0:r-1];
 reg [0:r-1]temp1_parity;
 reg [size-1:0] temp1_min1 [0:r-1];
 reg [size-1:0] temp1_min2 [0:r-1];
 reg temp1_parity_wire;
 reg [size-1:0]temp1_min1_wire;
 reg [size-1:0]temp1_min2_wire;
 
 
 wire [size-1:0] Rr_abs [0:c-1];
 reg signed[size-1:0] temp_Rnex [0:c-1];
 reg signed[size-1:0] Rnex [0:c-1];
 reg signed[size-1:0] R_row [0:c-1];
 
 localparam r_size = $clog2(r)+1;
 reg [r_size-1 : 0]st5_count;
 reg [r_size-1:0]m;
 reg [r_size-1:0]m1;
 reg llr_refining;
 reg min_parity;
 reg [3:0]state=0;
 
 
 //values for timer
 localparam d0=1 ,d1=1 ,d2=1 ,d3=1 ,d4=1 ,d5=r+1 ,d6=2 ,d7=1 ,d8=1 ; //delay clocks
 localparam t0=d0 ,t1=t0+d1 ,t2=t1+d2 ,t3=t2+d3 ,t4=t3+d4 ,t5=t4+d5 ,t6=t5+d6 ,t7=t6+d7 ,tf=t7+d8 ; //target clocks are made from dealy clocks
 localparam counter_size = $clog2(tf); // tf -> target final
 reg [tf:0]counter;
 
 
 
//absolute value for Rr
genvar n;
generate
for(n=0;n<c;n=n+1)begin
 assign Rr_abs[n] = Rr[n][size-1]?(~Rr[n]+1):Rr[n];
end
endgenerate

//Finding mins and parity of every row at once
genvar i;
generate
for(i=0;i<r;i=i+1)begin : MINS_PARITY
parity #(.size(size),.c(c)) u_parity(.R(Rr),.row(PCM[i]),.parity(temp_parity[i]));
mins #(.size(size),.c(c)) u_mins(.R(Rr),.row(PCM[i]),.min1(temp_min1[i]),.min2(temp_min2[i]));
end
endgenerate
 

// LLR refining and updating through updated rows
genvar l; //L->l
generate
for(l=0;l<c;l=l+1)begin : LLR_REFINING_UPDATING
always @(*)begin
if(llr_refining)begin 
  temp_Rnex[l]=Rr[l];
  for(integer k=0;k<r;k=k+1)begin 
      if(PCM[k][l] == 1'b1)begin
            if(Rr_abs[l]==min1[k])begin
                  if(Rr[l]<0)begin
                      if(parity[k] == 1'b1)
                          temp_Rnex[l] = temp_Rnex[l] + min2[k];
                      else
                          temp_Rnex[l] = temp_Rnex[l] - min2[k];
                      end
                  else begin
                      if(parity[k] == 1'b1)
                          temp_Rnex[l] = temp_Rnex[l] - min2[k];
                      else
                          temp_Rnex[l] = temp_Rnex[l] + min2[k];
                      end
                  end
            else begin
                  if(Rr[l]<0)begin
                      if(parity[k] == 1'b1)
                          temp_Rnex[l] = temp_Rnex[l] + min1[k];
                      else
                          temp_Rnex[l] = temp_Rnex[l] - min1[k];
                      end
                  else begin
                      if(parity[k] == 1'b1)
                          temp_Rnex[l] = temp_Rnex[l] - min1[k];
                      else
                          temp_Rnex[l] = temp_Rnex[l] + min1[k];
                      end
                  end
            end
        end
     end
  end
end
endgenerate

// Finding mins in updated columns
//for(m=0;m<r;m=m+1)begin
genvar j;
generate
for(j=0;j<c;j=j+1)begin : MIN_PARITY_FIND
    always@(posedge clk)begin
     R_row[j] = '{default:0};
     if(min_parity)begin
        if(PCM[m][j] == 1'b1)begin
            if(Rr_abs[j]==min1[m])begin
                if(Rr[j]<0)begin
                    if(parity[m]==1'b1)
                        R_row[j] <= Rnex[j] - min2[m];
                    else
                        R_row[j] <= Rnex[j] + min2[m];
                    end
                else begin
                    if(parity[m]==1'b1)
                        R_row[j] <= Rnex[j] + min2[m];
                    else
                        R_row[j] <= Rnex[j] - min2[m];
                    end
                end
            else begin
                if(Rr[j]<0)begin
                    if(parity[m]==1'b1)
                        R_row[j] <= Rnex[j] - min1[m];
                    else
                        R_row[j] <= Rnex[j] + min1[m];
                    end
                else begin
                    if(parity[m]==1'b1)
                        R_row[j] <= Rnex[j] + min1[m];
                    else
                        R_row[j] <= Rnex[j] - min1[m];
                    end
                end
            end
        end
      end
  end
 endgenerate
 
 assign m1 = m-1;
 parity #(.size(size),.c(c)) u1_parity(.R(R_row),.row(PCM[m1]),.parity(temp1_parity_wire));
 mins #(.size(size),.c(c)) u1_mins(.R(R_row),.row(PCM[m1]),.min1(temp1_min1_wire),.min2(temp1_min2_wire));
 
always @(posedge clk)begin
 temp1_min1[m1] <= temp1_min1_wire;
 temp1_min2[m1] <= temp1_min2_wire;
 temp1_parity[m1] <= temp1_parity_wire;
end






//Control Unit
always @(posedge clk)begin
 case(state)
  4'd0: begin //1clk
            min1 <= '{default:0};
            min2 <= '{default:0};
            parity <= {r{1'b0}};
            llr_refining <= 1'b0;
            min_parity <= 1'b0;
            Rr <= '{default:0};
            Rnex <= '{default:0};
            st5_count <= {r_size{1'b0}};
            out_start <= 1'b0;
        end
  4'd1: Rr <= R; //1clk
  4'd2: begin //nclk
            parity <= temp_parity;
            min1 <= temp_min1;
            min2 <= temp_min2;
        end
  4'd3: llr_refining <= 1'b1; //nclk
  4'd4: begin //1clk
            Rnex <= temp_Rnex;
            llr_refining <= 1'b0;
        end
  4'd5: begin //r+1clk
            if(st5_count == {r_size{1'b0}})begin
                min_parity <= 1'b1;
                m <= {r_size{1'b0}};
                st5_count <= st5_count + 1'b1;
                end
            else if(st5_count < r)begin
                m <= m + 1'b1;  
                st5_count <= st5_count + 1'b1;
                end
            else if(st5_count == r)begin
                min_parity <= 1'b0;
                st5_count <= {r_size{1'b0}};
                m <= m + 1'b1;
                end
            else st5_count <= {r_size{1'b0}};
        end
  4'd6: begin //2clk
            //min_parity <= 1'b0;
            parity <= temp1_parity;
            min1 <= temp1_min1;
            min2 <= temp1_min2;
        end
  4'd7: begin
            Rr <= Rnex; //1clk
        end
  4'd8: out_start <= 1'b1;//1clk
  endcase
 end
 
 //Decison making for Output decoded message
 genvar k;
 generate
 for(k=0;k<r;k=k+1)begin
 assign message[k] = (Rr[k]<0)?1'b1:1'b0; 
 end
 endgenerate
 
 
         
//Timing Unit
  
 always @(posedge clk)begin
  if(!rstb)state <= 4'd0; //reset stage
  else if(counter == t0)state <= 4'd1;
  else if(counter == t1)state <= 4'd2;
  else if(counter == t2)state <= 4'd3;
  else if(counter == t3)state <= 4'd4;
  else if(counter == t4)state <= 4'd5;
  else if(counter == t5)state <= 4'd6;
  else if(counter == t6)state <= 4'd7;
  else if(counter == t7)state <= 4'd8;
  else if(counter == tf)state <= 4'd0;
  //else state <= 3'd0;
 end
  
 always @(posedge clk)begin //counter generator for reference clocks passed and starts only when in_start signal is pulsed
  if(!rstb)begin
            counter <= {counter_size{1'b0}};
            nn <= 0;
           end
  else if(counter == 0 && in_start == 1'b1)counter <= {{counter_size-1{1'b0}},1'b1};
  else if (counter>0 && counter < t6)counter <= counter + 1'b1;
  else if(counter == t6)begin
            if(nn<(N-1))begin
                        counter <= t2;
                        nn <= nn+1;
                    end
            else begin
                    counter <= counter + 1'b1;
                    nn <= 0;
                 end
                   end
  else if (counter>0 && counter < tf)counter <= counter + 1'b1;
  else counter <= {counter_size{1'b0}};
 end
